wsInfraClusterMIB.description: The Cluster module is responsible for providing a minimal interrupted service to the network in the case of a switch failure by making the other standby switch take over the un-adopted Access ports. The core functionalities of the Cluster module are as listed below: - Manage and process automatic port adoption by switch(es) in the event of network or any switch failure. - Manage the cluster license. - Act as a tunnel between the application modules of CC across the switches. All Cluster related configuration parameters (except of course wsInfraClusterEnable itself) can be modified only if Cluster Protocol is disabled.

wsInfraClusterSwitchIP.name: wsInfraClusterSwitchIP
wsInfraClusterSwitchIP.description: The IP Address of the switch in the cluster context.

wsInfraClusterEnable.name: wsInfraClusterEnable
wsInfraClusterEnable.description: Enable or disable the Cluster feature.

wsInfraClusterMode.name: wsInfraClusterMode
wsInfraClusterMode.description: Set the mode to either Active or Standby. This object can not be set when Cluster feature is enabled. Disable the Cluster feature using wsInfraClusterEnable before setting this object.

wsInfraClusterId.name: wsInfraClusterId
wsInfraClusterId.description: Cluster/Group id. This object can not be set when Cluster feature is enabled. Disable the Cluster feature using wsInfraClusterEnable before setting this object.

wsInfraClusterDiscoveryInterval.name: wsInfraClusterDiscoveryInterval
wsInfraClusterDiscoveryInterval.description: During this time switches try to discover other switches in the cluster. This object can not be set when Cluster feature is enabled. Disable the Cluster feature using wsInfraClusterEnable before setting this object.

wsInfraClusterHoldInterval.name: wsInfraClusterHoldInterval
wsInfraClusterHoldInterval.description: Time to announce that the neighbour switch is down if no heartbeats received during this period of time. This object can not be set when Cluster feature is enabled. Disable the Cluster feature using wsInfraClusterEnable before setting this object.

wsInfraClusterHBInterval.name: wsInfraClusterHBInterval
wsInfraClusterHBInterval.description: The frequency in which heartbeats are sent. This object can not be set when Cluster feature is enabled. Disable the Cluster feature using wsInfraClusterEnable before setting this object.

wsInfraClusterHandleSTP.name: wsInfraClusterHandleSTP
wsInfraClusterHandleSTP.description: Whether the STP convergence time needs to be handled or not.

wsInfraClusterHistoryEntry.name: wsInfraClusterHistoryEntry

wsInfraClusterHistoryTime.name: wsInfraClusterHistoryTime

wsInfraClusterFirstSeen.name: wsInfraClusterFirstSeen

wsInfraClusterNumUpdMesgSent.name: wsInfraClusterNumUpdMesgSent

wsInfraClusterAutoRevert.name: wsInfraClusterAutoRevert
wsInfraClusterAutoRevert.description: Enable or disable automatic revert. This object can not be set when Cluster feature is enabled. Disable the Cluster feature using wsInfraClusterEnable before setting this object.

wsInfraClusterAutoRevertDelay.name: wsInfraClusterAutoRevertDelay
wsInfraClusterAutoRevertDelay.description: Auto-revert delay (in minutes - ranging from 1 to 1800). This object can not be set when Cluster feature is enabled. Disable the Cluster feature using wsInfraClusterEnable before setting this object.

wsInfraClusterDhcpRedundancy.name: wsInfraClusterDhcpRedundancy
wsInfraClusterDhcpRedundancy.description: Enable or disable the DHCP redundancy feature. This object can not be set when Cluster feature is enabled. Disable the Cluster feature using wsInfraClusterEnable before setting this object.

wsInfraClusterActiveDhcpServerSwitch.name: wsInfraClusterActiveDhcpServerSwitch
wsInfraClusterActiveDhcpServerSwitch.description: IP address of the switch running the active DHCP server. Other values this field could take are: NotApplicable - when redundancy is disabled. Unknown - when at any given time if there is no active DHCP server switch or the current switch is not participating in DHCP redundancy.

wsInfraClusterResetActiveDhcpServer.name: wsInfraClusterResetActiveDhcpServer
wsInfraClusterResetActiveDhcpServer.description: Reset the active DHCP server. If the current switch is running active DHCP server, then the DHCP server will be reset. Otherwise, this action will be ignored.

wsInfraCriticalResourceIp.name: wsInfraCriticalResourceIp
wsInfraCriticalResourceIp.description: IP address of the Critical Resource for the cluster switches. This object can not be set when Cluster feature is enabled. Disable the Cluster feature using wsInfraClusterEnable before setting this object.

wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalEnable.name: wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalEnable
wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalEnable.description: Enable or disable dynamic AP load balance feature. Default is disabled.

wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalApproach.name: wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalApproach
wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalApproach.description: This determines whether to the trigger dynamic AP load balance on scheduled time or immediately when AP imbalance is detected.

wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalSchedStartTime.name: wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalSchedStartTime
wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalSchedStartTime.description: If trigger for dynamic AP load balance is scheduled time then this configuration parameter determines the start time to initiate dynamic AP load balance.

wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalSchedInterval.name: wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalSchedInterval
wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalSchedInterval.description: If trigger for dynamic AP load balance is scheduled time then this configuration parameter determines the interval or frequency at which dynamic AP load balance will be triggered. Default value is 1 day.

wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalStart.name: wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalStart
wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalStart.description: Command to initiate dynamic AP load balance.

wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalMUThrshld.name: wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalMUThrshld
wsInfraClusterDynApLoadBalMUThrshld.description: This specifies per AP MU threshold value. If AP associated MU count is equal to or greater than this threshold value then AP will not be reset. It also depends on trigger for dynamic AP load balance. Default value is 32 MUs.

wsInfraClusterLicensingAlgorithm.name: wsInfraClusterLicensingAlgorithm
wsInfraClusterLicensingAlgorithm.description: Set the redundancy licensing algorithm to either Max or Aggregation. This object can not be set when Redundancy feature is enabled. Disable the Redundancy feature using wsInfraClusterEnable before setting this object.
